; Regression test for issue #1786: Parsing of metadata with multiple semicolons
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1786
;
; When a posting comment begins with multiple `;` characters (optionally
; separated by whitespace), the extra semicolons must be treated as part
; of the comment prefix -- not glued onto the following tag name.  The
; related fix for issue #1702 addressed the tag value offset but left
; the tag name corrupted in these cases:
;
;   ;;Key: Value      -> tag was ";Key", now "Key"
;   ;  ;Key: Value    -> tag was ";Key", now "Key"
;   ;;;Key: Value     -> tag was ";;Key", now "Key"
;
; Bare-tag syntax (`:tag1:tag2:`) must also keep working through the
; extra semicolons.

2019-04-16 * Metadata with space-separated double semicolon
    ;  ;Foo: Bar
    Assets:Test         10.00 EUR
    Income:Test        -10.00 EUR

2019-04-16 * Metadata with consecutive double semicolons
    ;;Test: Baz
    Assets:Test         10.00 EUR
    Income:Test        -10.00 EUR

2019-04-16 * Metadata with three consecutive semicolons
    ;;;Triple: Quux
    Assets:Test         10.00 EUR
    Income:Test        -10.00 EUR

2019-04-16 * Bare tags behind double semicolons
    ;;:alpha:beta:
    Assets:Test         10.00 EUR
    Income:Test        -10.00 EUR

test tags
Foo
Test
Triple
alpha
beta
end test

test tags --values
Foo: Bar
Test: Baz
Triple: Quux
alpha
beta
end test
